[01:55.60]Transverse to the length were innumerable tables made of slabs of polished stone, raised, perhaps, a foot from the floor, and upon these were heaps of fruits.  Some I recognised as a kind of hypertrophied raspberry（山莓） and orange, but for the most part they were strange. 
大厅里横放着许多磨光的石板桌，桌面离地约有1英尺，上面堆满了水果，其中有些水果我认出来，是肥大的紫莓和桔子，但大部分水果我不认识。

[02:14.22]"Between the tables was scattered a great number of cushions.  Upon these my conductors seated themselves, signing for me to do likewise.  With a pretty absence of ceremony they began to eat the fruit with their hands, flinging peel and stalks, and so forth, into the round openings in the sides of the tables. 
